README: PYTHIN BINDING WITH SWIG


Manual Python binding with swig on Linux:
   $ swig -c++ -python -o libgexf_wrap.cpp libgexf.i
   $ gcc -fPIC -c libgexf_wrap.cpp ../../graph.cpp ${OTHER_CPP_FILES} -I/usr/include/python2.5
   $ g++ -shared libgexf_wrap.o graph.o gexf.o -o _libgexf.so

Automated Python binding with swig on Linux:
   $ swig -c++ -python -o libgexf_wrap.cpp libgexf.i
   $ python setup.py build


To use :
   $ ipython
    >>> import libgexf
    >>> from libgexf import *
    >>> g = GEXF()
   ...

To test:
  Copy the test.py file into the appropriate build directory.
  Change the python version if necessary.
  Edit the gexf input file.
  $ ./test.py

To install:
   $ sudo python setup.py install

to build
    $ python setup.py build
   
to distribute
    $ python setup.py sdist

